Activity 2: Fruit Stamping

Age Group: 2-5 years old
Category(s): sensory exploration, motor coordination, color mixing and painting techniques. 

Materials: Apples or pears cut in half, paper plates, acrylic paints, and paper.
Instructions:  Pour a little paint on paper plates. Dip the cut side of the fruit into the paint and then stamp it onto the paper. Have 
children observe the shapes and patterns it creates.

Learning Goals: Develop fine motor skills and hand-eye coordination while grasping larger fruits and realizing the patterns they create.

Adapt: 1-1.5 year old babies can participate in this activity with supervision, edible painting is better for them. 

Monserrat's Tip: For 6+ years old you can encourage them to combine different painting materiasl and patern making for more creative designs

