Activity 7: Marble Painting

Age Group: 2–12 years (focus changes according to age)

Category(s): Art, creativity, color exploration, fine motor coordination.

Materials: Cardboard box or tray, white paper, marbles, washable paint.

Instructions: Place paper inside the box. Dip marbles in paint and gently tilt the box so they roll across the paper creating colorful trails.

What We'll Learn: Develop hand-eye coordination, explore movement and cause and effect, and express creativity.

ADApt: Use one marble and one color for younger children. Older children can create patterns or simple paths.

Monserrat's Tip: See what shapes appear in the paint trails—maybe rivers, fireworks, or magical forests!

Safety Notes: Marbles are a choking hazard. Adult supervision is required.

Video Script: (To be completed by Lilian.)

Reference / Inspiration: Traditional preschool marble painting activity.

