Activity 13: Paper Plate Animal Masks

Age Group:
3–12 years

Category(s):
Creative Art, Dramatic Play, Fine Motor Skills

Materials:
Paper plates, crayons or markers, child-safe scissors, glue, craft paper, yarn or craft sticks, elastic string (optional), stickers, feathers or pom-poms (optional).

Instructions:
Choose your favorite animal. Decorate a paper plate to create its face using crayons, markers, and craft materials. Cut out eye holes with an adult's help if needed. Attach a craft stick or elastic string to wear the mask. When finished, pretend to be your animal and create a fun story together.

What We'll Learn:
Encourage imagination and storytelling. Practice cutting, coloring, and gluing skills. Learn about different animals and their features.
Build confidence through creative play.

ADApt
Prepare the eye holes before the activity if needed. Children who find scissors challenging can decorate pre-cut mask templates. Offer adaptive scissors or larger craft pieces when appropriate.

Monserrat's Tip
Give your animal a silly name and a special voice. The best stories begin with a little imagination!

Safety Notes
Use child-safe scissors and supervise cutting activities. Make sure masks fit comfortably and do not block vision.

Paper Plate Animal Masks Video Script
(To be completed by Lilian.)

Reference / Inspiration

Primary Source:
