Activity 15: Recycled Robot Challenge

Age Group:
4–12 years

Category(s):
Creative Art, STEAM, Engineering, Imaginative Play

Materials:
Clean recycled boxes, paper tubes, bottle caps, egg cartons, child-safe glue, tape, markers, googly eyes (optional), child-safe scissors.

Instructions:
Gather clean recycled materials from around your home. Imagine what kind of robot you would like to build. Glue or tape the pieces together to create your robot, then decorate it with markers, stickers, or other craft materials. Give your robot a name and think about what special job it could do to help people.

What We'll Learn
Encourage creativity and problem-solving.
Explore basic engineering through building.
Practice planning and decision-making.
Discover new ways to reuse everyday materials.
ADApt

Offer larger recycled materials that are easier to hold. Children can work with a partner or an adult to assemble the robot if needed. Instead of cutting pieces, provide pre-cut materials for younger children.

Monserrat's Tip

What would your robot do? Maybe it waters plants, helps clean up toys, tells funny jokes, or gives hugs. Every robot has its own special talent!

Safety Notes
Use only clean, child-safe recycled materials. Remove any sharp edges before beginning. Adult supervision is recommended during assembly.

Recycled Robot Challenge Video Script
